    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/port-facility-security-officer-training-list-of-approved-training-providers"/>
    <title>Port facility security officer training - list of approved training providers</title>
    <category>Publication</category>
    <summary>A list of approved training providers for Port Security Officer training (PFSO)</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;All Port Facility Security Officers (PFSOs) in the UK must attend an approved training course run by an accredited company. The companies in this document have thus far been accredited and received approval from the Department for Transport to conduct &lt;abbr title="Port Facility Security Officers"&gt;PFSO&lt;/abbr&gt; training courses on behalf of the industry. All courses may be subject to unannounced audits by the Department for Transport to ensure quality control. Additional training providers will be added to the list as they receive approval.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To apply to become an accredited training provider please contact:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="address"&gt;&lt;div class="adr org fn"&gt;&lt;p&gt;

Maritime Training Manager  
&lt;br&gt;Department for Transport  
&lt;br&gt;Great Minster House  
&lt;br&gt;33 Horseferry Road  
&lt;br&gt;London SW1P 4DR  
&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Telephone 0300 330 3000&lt;br&gt;
email: &lt;a href="mailto:maritimesecurity@dft.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;maritimesecurity@dft.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details of training for Ship Security Officers (SSOs) and Company Security Officers (CSOs) can be found on the &lt;a rel="external" href="http://www.dft.gov.uk/mca/mcga07-home/mcga-mgn"&gt;MCA website&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
